{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \deftab720 \pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\qj
\f0\fs52 \cf0 Several molecular approaches are able to focus the large number of short reads provided by modern sequencing platforms on specific, restriction enzyme-anchored positions in the genome. This family of reduced representation genotyping approaches, generically called genotype-by-sequencing (GBS) or restriction site-associated DNA sequencing (RAD-seq), enables the analysis of tens of thousands of genetic markers in scores of populations.\ \ Population genomics using GBS allows classic problems in ecological and evolutionary genetics, such as identification of parentage and relatedness, migration and gene flow, population structure and phylogeography, and phylogenetic reconstruction, to be addressed with unprecedented power and precision.\ \ The sizes of these GBS data sets now pose significant data processing and analytical challenges. Bioinformatics algorithms \'96 for generating population genomic statistics, structural analyses, or phylogenetic trees \'96 are not effective without human interpretation and these interpretations cannot be done unless large data sets can be properly visualized and presented to the experimenter. \ \ Here we describe \b vStacks \b0 , a Mac Application which will soon be available through Apple\'92s App Store. vStacks is used to view and annotate data analyzed by the Stacks pipeline - a population genomics software package. vStacks gives the experimenter a visualization of thousands of loci and their polymorphisms in scores of populations and hundreds of individuals.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \deftab720 \pard\pardeftab720\li560\fi-560\sl288\slmult1\qj
\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 1) \b0 Raw sequence reads are demultiplexed and cleaned (process_radtags).\
\b 2) \b0 Data from each individual are grouped into loci, and polymorphic nucleotide sites are identified (ustacks or pstacks for unaligned or aligned data, respectively).\
\b 3) \b0 Loci are grouped together across individuals and a catalogue is written (cstacks).\
\b 4) \b0 Loci from each individual are matched against the catalogue to determine the allelic state at each locus in each individual (sstacks).\
\b 5) \b0 Allelic states are either converted into a set of mappable genotypes (for a genetic map) using genotypes or subjected to population genetic statistics via populations, with the results being written in one or several useful output files.}
